## Risk Register Overview

### Risk Scoring Matrix
| Impact Level | Description | Score |
|--------------|-------------|-------|
| **Critical** | Project failure, safety issues, >$100K loss, >3 month delay | 5 |
| **High** | Major feature loss, $50K-$100K loss, 1-3 month delay | 4 |
| **Medium** | Performance degradation, $10K-$50K loss, 2-4 week delay | 3 |
| **Low** | Minor issues, <$10K loss, <2 week delay | 2 |
| **Minimal** | Negligible impact | 1 |

| Probability | Description | Score |
|-------------|-------------|-------|
| **Very High** | >70% chance of occurring | 5 |
| **High** | 50-70% chance | 4 |
| **Medium** | 30-50% chance | 3 |
| **Low** | 10-30% chance | 2 |
| **Very Low** | <10% chance | 1 |

**Risk Level = Impact Ã— Probability**
- 15-25: Critical (Red) - Immediate escalation required
- 10-14: High (Orange) - Active mitigation required
- 5-9: Medium (Yellow) - Monitor and plan mitigation
- 1-4: Low (Green) - Accept or monitor

---

## 1. Supply Chain & Procurement Risks

### RISK-SC-001: Component Obsolescence
- **Description**: Critical component announced EOL (End of Life) during development
- **Category**: Supply Chain
- **Impact**: High (4) - Requires redesign, BOM changes, requalification
- **Probability**: Medium (3) - Common in semiconductor/electronic components
- **Risk Level**: 12 (High) ðŸŸ 
- **Risk Owner**: Supply Chain Manager
- **Affected Assets**: [e.g., "Main MCU STM32F4, Motor Driver IC"]
- **Mitigation Strategy**:
  - [ ] Select components with >5 year production lifecycle guarantee
  - [ ] Identify alternate parts during design phase (second source)
  - [ ] Subscribe to vendor PCN (Product Change Notification) alerts
  - [ ] Maintain strategic inventory for long-lead components
- **Contingency Plan**: Pre-qualified alternate MCU (Nordic nRF52) with firmware portability layer
- **Status**: Active | **Last Review**: [DATE]
- **Notes**: [Additional context]

---

### RISK-SC-002: Single-Source Supplier Dependency
- **Description**: Critical component available from only one supplier with no alternatives
- **Category**: Supply Chain
- **Impact**: Critical (5) - Production halt if supplier fails
- **Probability**: Low (2) - Supplier financially stable but geopolitical risks
- **Risk Level**: 10 (High) ðŸŸ 
- **Risk Owner**: Supply Chain Manager
- **Affected Assets**: [e.g., "Custom BLDC motor from Vendor X"]
- **Mitigation Strategy**:
  - [ ] Negotiate minimum inventory buffer (12 weeks stock)
  - [ ] Develop second-source qualification plan
  - [ ] Design motor mount to accommodate alternate motor dimensions (Â±5mm tolerance)
  - [ ] Establish quarterly supplier health reviews
- **Contingency Plan**: Fallback to commercial off-the-shelf motor with 80% performance
- **Status**: Active | **Last Review**: [DATE]

---

### RISK-SC-003: Extended Lead Times
- **Description**: Key components have 16+ week lead times, risking schedule delays
- **Category**: Supply Chain
- **Impact**: High (4) - Delays EVT/DVT schedule by 4-8 weeks
- **Probability**: High (4) - Current semiconductor shortage environment
- **Risk Level**: 16 (Critical) ðŸ”´
- **Risk Owner**: Supply Chain Manager + Hardware Lead
- **Affected Assets**: [e.g., "Battery cells, custom magnetics, injection molded enclosure"]
- **Mitigation Strategy**:
  - [ ] Place advance purchase orders during design phase
  - [ ] Use rapid prototyping (3D print, CNC) for early builds instead of waiting for tooling
  - [ ] Stagger component orders to match critical path
  - [ ] Establish safety stock policy (4-6 weeks buffer)
- **Contingency Plan**: Use development kits/EVT with alternate components until production parts arrive
- **Status**: Critical | **Last Review**: [DATE]

---

### RISK-SC-004: Cost Volatility
- **Description**: Component pricing fluctuates >20% affecting BOM targets
- **Category**: Supply Chain / Financial
- **Impact**: Medium (3) - Erodes margin or requires pricing adjustment
- **Probability**: Medium (3) - Commodity materials (aluminum, copper, batteries) volatile
- **Risk Level**: 9 (Medium) ðŸŸ¡
- **Risk Owner**: Supply Chain Manager + Finance
- **Mitigation Strategy**:
  - [ ] Lock in pricing with long-term agreements (LTA) for high-volume components
  - [ ] Design margin buffer (15-20% cost contingency)
  - [ ] Identify cost-reduction opportunities (value engineering)
  - [ ] Monitor commodity indices weekly
- **Contingency Plan**: Reduce features or shift to lower-cost materials if BOM exceeds target
- **Status**: Monitor | **Last Review**: [DATE]

---

## 2. Technical & Engineering Risks

### RISK-TE-001: Thermal Management Failure
- **Description**: Sustained operation causes CPU/motor drivers to exceed thermal limits (>85Â°C)
- **Category**: Technical - Hardware
- **Impact**: Critical (5) - Safety hazard, component damage, reduced lifespan
- **Probability**: Medium (3) - Unknown until environmental testing
- **Risk Level**: 15 (Critical) ðŸ”´
- **Risk Owner**: Hardware Lead + Mechanical Engineer
- **Affected Assets**: [e.g., "Motor driver PCB, CPU module, battery pack"]
- **Mitigation Strategy**:
  - [ ] Thermal simulation (CFD analysis) during design phase
  - [ ] Oversized heatsinks and forced air cooling (2x 40mm fans)
  - [ ] Thermal testing at EVT phase (72hr soak test at 50Â°C ambient)
  - [ ] Implement thermal throttling in firmware as safety backstop
- **Contingency Plan**: Mechanical redesign to add ventilation ports, upgrade to higher-temp rated components
- **Status**: Active | **Last Review**: [DATE]

---

### RISK-TE-002: EMI/EMC Compliance Failure
- **Description**: Product fails FCC Part 15 Class B or CE EMC testing
- **Category**: Technical - Regulatory
- **Impact**: High (4) - Cannot ship to market, requires costly redesign
- **Probability**: Medium (3) - Complex digital + motor circuitry
- **Risk Level**: 12 (High) ðŸŸ 
- **Risk Owner**: Hardware Lead + Compliance Engineer
- **Mitigation Strategy**:
  - [ ] EMI pre-compliance testing at EVT phase (in-house or 3rd party)
  - [ ] Design best practices: ground planes, shielding, filtering, cable routing
  - [ ] Budget for 2x EMC test cycles (initial + retest after fixes)
  - [ ] Engage EMC consultant early in layout phase
- **Contingency Plan**: Add ferrite beads, EMI gaskets, shielded enclosure (adds $15-30 BOM cost)
- **Status**: Active | **Last Review**: [DATE]

---

### RISK-TE-003: HW/SW Integration Issues
- **Description**: Firmware/software integration reveals hardware design flaws requiring PCB respin
- **Category**: Technical - Integration
- **Impact**: High (4) - 4-6 week delay for PCB redesign + fabrication
- **Probability**: Medium (3) - First-time integration of complex subsystems
- **Risk Level**: 12 (High) ðŸŸ 
- **Risk Owner**: Hardware Lead + Firmware Lead
- **Mitigation Strategy**:
  - [ ] Component-level testing before integration (test each sensor/actuator standalone)
  - [ ] Use development boards for early firmware prototyping
  - [ ] Daily standups between HW/FW teams during integration phase
  - [ ] Build engineering prototypes with debug headers and test points
- **Contingency Plan**: Rework/flying wires for minor fixes, green-wire boards for DVT if needed
- **Status**: Active | **Last Review**: [DATE]

---

### RISK-TE-004: Mechanical Tolerance Stack-Up
- **Description**: Accumulated tolerances cause fit/assembly issues (parts don't align, excessive gaps)
- **Category**: Technical - Mechanical
- **Impact**: Medium (3) - Cosmetic issues, assembly difficulty, yield loss
- **Probability**: Medium (3) - Complex multi-part assembly
- **Risk Level**: 9 (Medium) ðŸŸ¡
- **Risk Owner**: Mechanical Engineer
- **Mitigation Strategy**:
  - [ ] Tolerance analysis (worst-case and statistical) during design
  - [ ] Design for wider tolerances where possible (Â±0.3mm instead of Â±0.1mm)
  - [ ] Prototype with production-intent processes (SLA for early, CNC for EVT, tooling for DVT)
  - [ ] DFM review with manufacturing partner
- **Contingency Plan**: Adjust CAD models, recut tooling (expensive but necessary)
- **Status**: Monitor | **Last Review**: [DATE]

---

### RISK-TE-005: Battery Safety & Certification
- **Description**: Lithium battery fails safety testing (UN38.3, IEC 62133) or presents fire hazard
- **Category**: Technical - Safety
- **Impact**: Critical (5) - Cannot ship, liability exposure, product recall
- **Probability**: Low (2) - Using certified battery cells from Tier-1 supplier
- **Risk Level**: 10 (High) ðŸŸ 
- **Risk Owner**: Hardware Lead + Compliance Engineer
- **Mitigation Strategy**:
  - [ ] Use pre-certified battery packs from reputable suppliers
  - [ ] Implement battery management system (BMS) with overcharge/discharge/thermal protection
  - [ ] Conduct abuse testing (overcharge, short circuit, drop test) at EVT
  - [ ] Obtain battery certifications early (12+ week lead time)
- **Contingency Plan**: Switch to lower capacity but fully certified battery pack
- **Status**: Active | **Last Review**: [DATE]

---

## 3. Manufacturing & Scaling Risks

### RISK-MF-001: Low Manufacturing Yield
- **Description**: Factory yield <85% due to assembly complexity or component sensitivity
- **Category**: Manufacturing
- **Impact**: High (4) - Increased COGS, delivery delays, customer quality issues
- **Probability**: Medium (3) - Complex assembly with 50+ components
- **Risk Level**: 12 (High) ðŸŸ 
- **Risk Owner**: Manufacturing Engineer + CM
- **Mitigation Strategy**:
  - [ ] Design for Manufacturing (DFM) review before tooling release
  - [ ] Pilot build at DVT phase (50-100 units) to identify yield issues
  - [ ] Develop detailed assembly SOPs with photos/videos
  - [ ] Implement test fixtures for in-line testing (not just final test)
- **Contingency Plan**: Simplify assembly (reduce part count), add poka-yoke features
- **Status**: Active | **Last Review**: [DATE]

---

### RISK-MF-002: CM Capacity Constraints
- **Description**: Contract manufacturer cannot scale to required production volume (target: 5K units/month)
- **Category**: Manufacturing / Supply Chain
- **Impact**: High (4) - Cannot meet customer demand, lose market window
- **Probability**: Low (2) - CM pre-qualified with 10K/month capacity
- **Risk Level**: 8 (Medium) ðŸŸ¡
- **Risk Owner**: Operations + Supply Chain Manager
- **Mitigation Strategy**:
  - [ ] Verify CM capacity during vendor selection (site visit + reference checks)
  - [ ] Ramp production gradually: 1K â†’ 2K â†’ 5K units/month
  - [ ] Identify backup CM (qualified as secondary)
  - [ ] Lock in capacity with advance purchase commitments
- **Contingency Plan**: Split production across two CMs (adds complexity)
- **Status**: Monitor | **Last Review**: [DATE]

---

### RISK-MF-003: Quality Escapes (OOB Failures)
- **Description**: Out-of-box (OOB) failure rate >2% due to inadequate factory testing
- **Category**: Manufacturing / Quality
- **Impact**: Critical (5) - Customer dissatisfaction, returns, brand damage
- **Probability**: Medium (3) - First production run always has infant mortality
- **Risk Level**: 15 (Critical) ðŸ”´
- **Risk Owner**: QA Lead + Manufacturing Engineer
- **Mitigation Strategy**:
  - [ ] Develop comprehensive factory test plan (functional + stress tests)
  - [ ] Implement burn-in testing (24-48hr power-on soak)
  - [ ] Strict QC documentation (tolerances, cosmetic acceptance criteria)
  - [ ] Sampling inspection: 100% test for first 500 units, then AQL 1.5% sampling
- **Contingency Plan**: 100% testing until yield stabilizes, RMA process for early returns
- **Status**: Critical | **Last Review**: [DATE]

---

## 4. Compliance & Regulatory Risks

### RISK-CR-001: Certification Delays
- **Description**: CE/FCC/UL certification testing delayed or requires resubmission
- **Category**: Compliance / Regulatory
- **Impact**: Critical (5) - Cannot launch product, miss market window
- **Probability**: Medium (3) - First submission often requires iterations
- **Risk Level**: 15 (Critical) ðŸ”´
- **Risk Owner**: Compliance Engineer
- **Mitigation Strategy**:
  - [ ] Engage test lab early, schedule testing 3 months before launch
  - [ ] Pre-compliance testing at DVT phase
  - [ ] Budget 6-8 weeks for test + iteration + certification issuance
  - [ ] Design margin into schedules for 1 retest cycle
- **Contingency Plan**: Ship to non-regulated markets first (B2B, industrial) while awaiting consumer certifications
- **Status**: Active | **Last Review**: [DATE]

---

### RISK-CR-002: Regulatory Requirements Change
- **Description**: New regulations imposed mid-development (e.g., updated RoHS, new safety standards)
- **Category**: Compliance / Regulatory
- **Impact**: High (4) - Requires design changes, requalification, delay
- **Probability**: Low (2) - Rare but possible for multi-year projects
- **Risk Level**: 8 (Medium) ðŸŸ¡
- **Risk Owner**: Compliance Engineer + Product Owner
- **Mitigation Strategy**:
  - [ ] Monitor regulatory changes (subscribe to industry alerts)
  - [ ] Design to current + anticipated future standards when possible
  - [ ] Maintain flexibility in design for minor compliance adjustments
- **Contingency Plan**: Delay launch to meet new requirements, or limit to markets with old regulations
- **Status**: Monitor | **Last Review**: [DATE]

---

## 5. Market & Business Risks

### RISK-MB-001: Market Timing Miss
- **Description**: Product launches after competitor or market demand shifts
- **Category**: Market / Business
- **Impact**: High (4) - Reduced revenue, harder sales, lower margins
- **Probability**: Medium (3) - 18-month development in fast-moving market
- **Risk Level**: 12 (High) ðŸŸ 
- **Risk Owner**: Product Owner + Executive Sponsor
- **Mitigation Strategy**:
  - [ ] Quarterly competitive analysis and market validation
  - [ ] MVP approach: launch with core features, add enhancements in v2
  - [ ] Maintain schedule discipline (weekly reviews, critical path management)
  - [ ] Consider soft launch / beta program to early customers
- **Contingency Plan**: Pivot product positioning, adjust pricing, or focus on underserved niche
- **Status**: Monitor | **Last Review**: [DATE]

---

### RISK-MB-002: Feature Creep
- **Description**: Stakeholders add features mid-development, causing scope expansion and delays
- **Category**: Business / Project Management
- **Impact**: Medium (3) - Schedule delay, cost overrun, team burnout
- **Probability**: High (4) - Common in startup/entrepreneurial environments
- **Risk Level**: 12 (High) ðŸŸ 
- **Risk Owner**: Project Manager + Product Owner
- **Mitigation Strategy**:
  - [ ] Lock requirements at Design Review gate (end of Engineering Prototype phase)
  - [ ] Formal change control process: all changes via ECO with impact assessment
  - [ ] Maintain product roadmap: defer non-critical features to v2
  - [ ] Weekly stakeholder alignment meetings
- **Contingency Plan**: Extend schedule, cut lower-priority features, or increase budget
- **Status**: Active | **Last Review**: [DATE]

